-To optimize CPU utilization while reading and generating flat files from a batch file that processes millions of records, consider the following design approaches:
-1. Implement Parallel Processing with Throttling
- Divide and Conquer: Instead of processing all records at once, split the workload into smaller batches and process them in parallel.
- Control Thread Count: Use a thread pool to limit the number of concurrent threads, preventing excessive CPU usage.
- Adjust Thread Priority: Lower thread priority to allow other critical processes to run smoothly.
-2. Optimize File Handling
- Use Buffered Reading/Writing: Avoid line-by-line reading/writing; use buffered I/O to reduce disk I/O overhead.
- Memory-Mapped Files: If the file size is very large, memory-mapped files can improve performance.
- Batch Writes: Accumulate records in memory and write in bulk instead of writing each record individually.
-3. Optimize Database Queries
- Use Indexed Queries: Ensure that database tables have proper indexing to speed up data retrieval.
- Fetch in Chunks: Use pagination techniques (e.g., LIMIT and OFFSET) to retrieve data in manageable chunks instead of fetching all records at once.
- Avoid Unnecessary Joins: Reduce complex joins or optimize queries to minimize processing time.
-4. Reduce Unnecessary Computation
