-To handle the forward slashes (/) in the file paths output by git diff on Windows, you can convert them to backslashes (\) so that the Windows copy command can work correctly. Here's how you can achieve this using a batch script.
-Batch Script to Convert and Copy Files
-This script will:
- Get the list of changed files using git diff.
- Convert the forward slashes to backslashes.
- Copy the files to a common folder.
-batch
-Copy
-@echo off
-setlocal enabledelayedexpansion
-
-REM Navigate to the repository directory
-cd "C:\path\to\your\repo"
-
-REM Get the list of changed files and write to a file
-git diff --name-only HEAD~1 HEAD > changed_files.txt
-
-REM Define the destination folder
-set "destination_folder=C:\path\to\common\folder"
-
-REM Ensure the destination folder exists
-if not exist "%destination_folder%" (
-    mkdir "%destination_folder%"
-)
-
-REM Loop through the list of changed files
-for /f "delims=" %%i in (changed_files.txt) do (
-    REM Replace forward slashes with backslashes
-    set "file=%%i"
-    set "file=!file:/=\!"
-
-    REM Copy the file to the destination folder
-    copy "!file!" "%destination_folder%"
-)
-
-REM Clean up
-del changed_files.txt
-
-endlocal
