- Navigate to Repository: Change the directory to your local repository.
- Get Changed Files: Use git diff --name-only HEAD~1 HEAD to get the list of changed files and write them to changed_files.txt.
- Define Destination Folder: Set the destination folder where the files will be copied.
- Ensure Destination Folder Exists: Create the folder if it doesn't already exist.
- Loop Through Changed Files: Read each file from changed_files.txt, convert forward slashes to backslashes, and copy the file to the destination folder.
- Clean Up: Delete the temporary changed_files.txt file.
